    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Mideast Peace, Derailed Again</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Charles S Hexter letter points out that right of all refugees to return is Palestinian euphemism for elimination of Jewish state, and no country willingly commits suicide; adds that peace will come when Jewish state is accepted by Palestinians</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Israel's Doomed Peace,'' by Allegra Pacheco (Op-Ed, Oct. 5):</p>
        <p>Ms. Pacheco is quite right that the Oslo process is doomed, and she inadvertently highlighted the reason.  The right of all refugees to return to their homeland is the Palestinian euphemism for the elimination of the Jewish state. No country willingly commits suicide, and neither will Israel.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Israel's Doomed Peace,'' by Allegra Pacheco (Op-Ed, Oct. 5):</p>
        <p>Ms. Pacheco is quite right that the Oslo process is doomed, and she inadvertently highlighted the reason.  The right of all refugees to return to their homeland is the Palestinian euphemism for the elimination of the Jewish state. No country willingly commits suicide, and neither will Israel.</p>
        <p>Peace will come when a Jewish state is accepted by the Palestinians.  CHARLES S. HEXTER  Rehovot, Israel, Oct. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
